criteria.exclusion_criteria:
There are other pathological conditions may cause abnormal vaginal bleeding, such as endometrial polyps, submucosal uterine fibroids, gynecological tumors;
1. generally poor, difficult to tolerate serious medical complications of hysteroscopic surgery;
2. reproductive system, urinary system, or with active systemic infection, surgery can be postponed until after the infection cleared;
3. coagulation disorders or are receiving therapeutic anticoagulation drugs;
4. The researchers believe there may be other medical or mental illness can not be with the completion of the investigator.
